          "description": "Excellent care!   Can't say enough about how glad I am that I found this place.  I have had a frequent recurring condition (urinary tract infections) and I feel I have finally gotten some answers and solutions.  I didn't know beforehand that I needed to take probiotics to prevent a yeast infection due to antibiotics or that HRT might be helpful.\n\nThe doctor I saw carefully considered my drug options so that they were safe to take with my other medications and tailored to the type of bacteria that was cultured.  Other doctors had just given me a pill - no explanations.\n\nI received written information regarding my conditions and the treatment plan. It is really a godsend to be able to get this kind of care and attention.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21GTWJGSnZWM0ZKVmtKdFJqRlhUMjlLTTBoMU5uYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa95d898b4d1f2351!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmFMbFJvV3FJVkJtRjFXT29KM0h1Nnc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "Edited a month ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-05-19T21:29:23+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Camille Needham",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "111355526428066161064",
          "user_review_count": 1,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocISf5WDvbkTRR01hG6gvlozIrwS9FLQ5I7LQZDXanf6w6f_2sSf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I came to this urgent care with severe low back and abdominal pain, unable to bend over at all and struggling to walk. I was seen by Dr. Gallane Abraham, and I can\u2019t think of another instance in my life where I\u2019ve felt so diminished by a doctor. She said I need to just take Advil and lay on a heating pad. I tried to explain to her just how severe the pain was, letting her know it was a 9/10 (though she did not ask). She just reiterated to take Advil and if I did feel better in a week or so to go see another doctor. In an effort to make her understand the urgency, I explained I was meant to be traveling in a few days for the holidays and didn\u2019t feel I would be able. She said \u201cif you can make it in here then you can make it to Atlanta\u201d. She rushed me out.\n\nLuckily, I was able to get in with my PCP the next day who instructed me to go to the ER immediately for a CT scan, as my symptoms were in line with potentially very dangerous conditions like appendicitis. In the end, I was experiencing rupturing ovarian cysts that I did not know I had.\n\nDo not come to this urgent care if you want your concerns to be taken remotely seriously or be treated with any sort of respect. My PCP, ER doctors, and OBGYN were all aghast at how Dr. Abraham treated me. I will say the receptionist Chelisa was lovely and in high spirits despite a packed waiting room and no assistance.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pOWExVODJOa0o2VVd4dmMxUnpOVjh4ZFd0b1RXYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa95d898b4d1f2351!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOjNXLU82NkJ6UWxvc1RzNV8xdWtoTWc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "Edited 6 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2025-12-23T23:19:11+00:00"
        },
